  "comment": "Octostrip MKII 100cm: The LED Octostrip MKII is the successor of the popular Octostrip. It is a complete plug-and-play set; consisting of 8 LED strips, a controller and eight 5-metre long XLR extension cables. The new LED Octostrip MKII can control each strip’s 8 individual RGB sections, along with the corresponding dimmer and strobe settings. The controller supports Art-Net protocol, which facilitates the use of device while operating in the full RGB mode (192-Ch mode). It has updated colour presets and built-in colour flows for use of horizontal and vertical directions which are accessible via DMX (in 6-Ch, 8-Ch, 14-Ch, 24-Ch, 26-Ch, 50CH,  192-Ch, 208-Ch channel modes). Because of the exact same hardware design It is possible to combine the Octostrip MKI to the new Octostrip MKII in one stage. However, in such case, it is not advisable to operate the old and the new version of the device in Auto mode, as the built-in programs differ per version. The 6-Ch mode has the same DMX channel settings to control both sets in one setup.",
